    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>BX-AI+ is a static, AI-centric Bootstrap 5 dashboard theme for Ortus Solutions BoxLang, designed for porting into a <strong>ColdBox 8.1+ module</strong> running on a BoxLang server. It ships as 50+ HTML pages plus an SCSS pipeline you can recompile and rebrand.</p>
      <p>The defining feature is the <strong>AI affordance layer</strong>: a topbar chat bar (⌘K command palette), a global voice toast, contextual "Ask AI" buttons on every widget, and an AI insights feed.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="install">
      <h2>Install &amp; build</h2>
      <p>Requires Node 20+. From the project root:</p>
<pre><code>npm install
npm run dev      # live-reload dev server at :3000
npm run build    # production build → dist/</code></pre>
      <p>Build output is plain HTML/CSS/JS in <code>dist/</code>. No server runtime is required to view the demo.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="structure">
      <h2>File structure</h2>
<pre><code>src/
├── html/         Eleventy input — pages, layouts, partials, _data
├── scss/         SCSS sources — config, components, structure, ai, pages, plugins
├── js/           JS modules — core, ai, components, pages, util
├── assets/       Images, fonts, brand marks
└── static/       Top-level static files
tools/            Build scripts (clean, css, js, asset copy)
dist/             Build output</code></pre>

      <h3>Adding a page</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Create <code>src/html/section/page.njk</code> with a front-matter block (<code>layout</code>, <code>title</code>, <code>permalink</code>, optional <code>page_module</code>).</li>
        <li>Add it to <code>src/html/_data/menu.json</code> if it should appear in the sidebar.</li>
        <li>If it needs page-specific JS, create <code>src/js/pages/page.js</code> and register it in the switch in <code>src/js/app.js</code>.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section id="tokens">
      <h2>Design tokens</h2>
      <p>All visual tokens live in <code>src/scss/config/_variables-custom.scss</code> and are emitted as CSS custom properties on <code>:root</code>. The full sheet is browseable at <a href="/__tokens/">/__tokens/</a>.</p>
      <table class="mb-3">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Default (dark)</th><th>Used for</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--bx-body-bg</code></td><td>#092221</td><td>Page background</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--bx-brand-primary</code></td><td>#0DD3A8</td><td>Primary accent, focus rings, active state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--bx-surface-1</code></td><td>#0E2D2B</td><td>Card / panel background</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--bx-text</code></td><td>#E6ECEF</td><td>Body text</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--bx-ai-gradient</code></td><td>teal → blue-purple → purple</td><td>AI-flavored emphasis</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section id="dark-light">
      <h2>Dark / light themes</h2>
      <p>Dark is the default. Light theme is a token pivot defined in <code>src/scss/config/_theme-mode.scss</code> and applied via <code>&lt;html data-bs-theme="light"&gt;</code>. The theme toggle in the topbar persists to <code>localStorage</code> so it survives reloads.</p>
      <p>To add a new theme variant, add a new <code>[data-bs-theme="…"]</code> selector in the same file and override the <code>--bx-*</code> tokens.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="layout-attrs">
      <h2>Layout attributes</h2>
      <p>Layout state lives on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> as <code>data-*</code> attributes. The customizer drawer reads / writes them and persists to <code>sessionStorage</code>.</p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Values</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>data-bs-theme</code></td><td><code>dark</code> / <code>light</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-layout</code></td><td><code>vertical</code> / <code>horizontal</code> (set by the layout file, navigation-driven)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-sidenav-size</code></td><td><code>default</code> / <code>compact</code> / <code>hover</code> / <code>offcanvas</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-sidenav-color</code></td><td><code>dark</code> / <code>light</code> / <code>brand</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data-topbar-color</code></td><td><code>dark</code> / <code>light</code> / <code>brand</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section id="widgets">
      <h2>Widget primitives</h2>
      <p>Reusable widgets live in <code>src/html/_includes/partials/widgets/</code> as Nunjucks macros:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>statCard(s)</code> — KPI card with sparkline + live counter (drift-driven)</li>
        <li><code>insightCard(insight)</code> — AI insight with anomaly / suggestion / query / summary variants</li>
        <li><code>widgetMenu(context, prompt)</code> — 3-dot overflow menu including "Ask AI about this"</li>
        <li><code>inlinePrompt(context, placeholder)</code> — embedded one-line AI prompt input</li>
      </ul>
<pre><code>{% raw %}{% from "partials/widgets/stat-card.njk" import statCard %}
{{ statCard(s) }}{% endraw %}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section id="ai">
      <h2>AI affordances</h2>
      <p>All four AI affordances are wired globally in <code>src/js/app.js</code>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Chat bar</strong> — the topbar pill, triggered by click or <kbd>⌘K</kbd>. Opens a command palette modal with live-filtered suggestions.</li>
        <li><strong>Voice toast</strong> — bottom-right, triggered by any <code>[data-bx-voice-trigger]</code>. State machine (idle → listening → processing → result → error) with a DOM-based waveform.</li>
        <li><strong>AI chat panel</strong> — right offcanvas, accepts queries from the chat bar, voice toast, and "Ask AI" buttons. Mock replies via <code>src/js/ai/mock-ai.js</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Ask AI</strong> — buttons everywhere with <code>data-bx-ai-ask</code> + <code>data-ai-context</code> + <code>data-ai-prompt</code>. Submits the prompt to the chat panel.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="charts">
      <h2>Charts</h2>
      <p>ApexCharts is the primary chart library. Theming hooks into our token system via <code>src/js/components/apex-defaults.js</code>:</p>
<pre><code>import { palette, themeSettings } from "./components/apex-defaults.js";

const t = themeSettings();
new ApexCharts(el, {
  chart: { ...t.chart, type: "line" },
  colors: palette(),
  grid: t.grid,
  xaxis: t.xaxis,
  yaxis: t.yaxis,
  legend: t.legend,
  tooltip: t.tooltip,
  series: [...]
});</code></pre>
      <p>Charts re-skin automatically on theme flip — pages with charts listen for <code>document.addEventListener("bx:layoutchange", …)</code>.</p>
    </section>

