    <section id="vendor-css">
      <h2>Vendor CSS pipeline</h2>
      <p>Plugin base CSS files are copied into <code>dist/assets/vendor/</code> by <code>tools/copy-assets.mjs</code>. A page opts into a vendor stylesheet via front-matter:</p>
<pre><code>---
pageVendorCss:
  - choices
  - flatpickr
  - quill.snow
---</code></pre>
      <p>BX-AI+ overrides for these libraries live in <code>src/scss/plugins/</code> and are loaded for every page via <code>app.css</code>, but the heavy structural CSS only loads where needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="seams">
      <h2>Seam markers</h2>
      <p>Every shared partial wraps its output with HTML comments via the <code>seamBegin</code> / <code>seamEnd</code> Eleventy shortcodes:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;!-- BEGIN :: TOPBAR --&gt;
... topbar markup ...
&lt;!-- END :: TOPBAR --&gt;</code></pre>
      <p>These survive Eleventy compilation and give the ColdBox module a mechanical find-and-replace path — each seam collapses to a single <code>#view( view="partials/...", module="bxaiplus" )#</code> call in the ColdBox layout. Search for <code>BEGIN ::</code> in any built HTML to see the full seam map.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="data-shape">
      <h2>Data shape</h2>
      <p>All page data comes from JSON files in <code>src/html/_data/</code> — the ColdBox module should emit identical shapes at runtime (via models, placed on <code>prc</code> by a handler or <code>preLayout</code> interceptor) to keep the templates working unchanged.</p>
      <p>Locked schemas: <code>menu.json</code>, <code>horizontalMenu.json</code>, <code>notifications.json</code>, <code>user.json</code>, <code>dashboard.json</code> (stats, charts, insights, activity), <code>aiAgents.json</code>, <code>aiPrompts.json</code>, <code>aiHistory.json</code>, plus per-app data (calendar, kanban, email, chat, files, projects).</p>
      <p>See <code>BOXLANG-PORT-NOTES.md</code> at the project root for the full porting guide — including the exact <code>view()</code> call per seam and the ColdBox module layout map.</p>
    </section>

